[@Powdery mildew of cucurbits#Disease*], incited by [$Podosphaera xanthii #Virus*]([@Castagne) Braun & Shishkoff #Virus*]([@syn.Sphaerotheca fuliginea auct.p.p.)#Virus*], is an economically important foliar disease.
which is now common in [$watermelon#Plant*] [[@Citrullus lanatus (Thunb.) Mastum.& Nakai#Virus*]].
This disease occurs in all [$watermelon#Plant*]-growing areas and can reduce yields by up to 30%.
Finding and breeding for resistance to this disease is important to reduce dependence on fungicides and to use in combination with fungicides to limit the spread of fungicide-resistant [$P.xanthii#Plant*].
This is the first English report that race 2WF of [$P.xanthii#Plant*] can infect [$watermelon#Plant*].
It is the prevalent race of [$watermelon#Plant*][$ powdery mildew#Virus*] in Beijing.
